"""Step-by-step walkthrough of the winning HCR and CZ surface-estimation
protocols, each illustrated on one representative subject.

HCR — subject 782149 (11 deg tilt shows global trend capture).
Steps visualised:
  1. All ROI centroids (z vs x, y-projection).
  2. Density-filtered ROIs (removes isolated buffer singletons).
  3. Per-tile minimum-z envelope (tiles = 120 um).
  4. Robust quadratic base fit through the envelope.
  5. Gaussian-smoothed tile residuals (sigma=120 um) added to the quad base.
  6. Final ceiling clamp + safety offset - surface on top of MIP.

CZ - subject 767022 (flat-ish, typical CZ).
Steps visualised:
  1. Combined z-stack MIP with raw image intensity.
  2. Per-column image-intensity ceiling (relative_margin=0.02).
  3. Per-tile ROI min-z envelope (80 um tiles).
  4. Plane clamp: lift image-plane above every ROI tile min-z.
"""
